The app uses a GraphQL API to fetch Pokémon data, specifically retrieving color information to randomly assign colors to the coins. GraphQL allows the app to request only the necessary fields (like color data) from the Pokémon API, avoiding over-fetching or under-fetching data compared to REST APIs. Here's a simplified example of how the GraphQL query might look:

graphql
query GetPokemonColor($id: Int!) {
  pokemon(id: $id) {
    color {
      name
    }
  }
}


The color data is then applied to the coins, adding variety and rarity to the visual experience.
